message.entry: Elements of input X must be integers in the range [0, M-1].
When InputType is set to 'Bit', elements of input X must be integers in the range [0, 1].
When InputType is set to 'Bit', the number of rows in the input X must be an integer multiple of the number of bits per symbol.
M must be a scalar positive integer.
M must be in the form of M = 2^K, where K is a positive integer.
INI_PHASE must be a real scalar.
Symbol order vector must have M elements.
Symbol order vector is only supported for Square QAM.
OutputDataType must be a signed, fixed-point numerictype or fi object.
OutputDataType must be a signed, fixed-point numerictype or fi object with specified scaling.
OutputDataType must be specified when input is of fixed-point datatype.
M must be less than or equal to 1024 for fixed-point output.
INI_PHASE is not supported in this form.
